<section id="import-example-web-service">
    <title>Import ready-to-run Web Services</title>

    <section>
        <title>Import</title>
        <para>
            There are three ready-to-run Web Services available in the <emphasis role="bold">OTRS Business Solutionâ„¢</emphasis>:
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        BugzillaConnector
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        JIRAConnector
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        OTRSConnector
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </para>
        <para>
            To install one of these web services, go to the <emphasis>GenericInterface Web Service Management</emphasis> page
            and click on the <emphasis>Add web service</emphasis> button.
        </para>
        <para>
            <figure>
                <title>Add web service</title>
                <screenshot>
                    <graphic fileref="screenshots/web-services/web-service-management.png" scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%"></graphic>
                </screenshot>
            </figure>
        </para>
        <para>
            Locate the <emphasis>Ready-to-run Web Services</emphasis> widget, select one of the provided web services from the drop-down menu, and click
            the <emphasis>Import ready-to-run Web Service</emphasis> button.
        </para>
        <para>
            <figure>
                <title>Import ready-to-run Web Service</title>
                <screenshot>
                    <graphic fileref="screenshots/web-services/import-example-web-service.png" scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%"></graphic>
                </screenshot>
            </figure>
        </para>
        <para>
            During the import process, OTRS takes care of creating the needed dynamic fields and/or any needed updates to the system configuration.
        </para>
        <note>
            <para>
                The ready-to-run Web Services may require additional feature add-ons to be installed (<emphasis role="bold">OTRSGenericInterfaceInvokerTicket</emphasis>
                and <emphasis role="bold">OTRSGenericInterfaceInvokerEventFilter</emphasis>).
            </para>
        </note>
    </section>
</section>
